
Examples

Here are some examples of using the User Management Script:

    To create a new user:

    perl

create_user("john.doe", "john.doe@example.com", "password123", "user")

To update an existing user:

bash

user_id = 123  # Replace with the actual user ID
updated_data = {
    'email': 'updated_email@example.com',
    'role': 'admin'
}
update_user(user_id, updated_data)

To delete a user:



user_id = 123  # Replace with the actual user ID
delete_user(user_id)

To retrieve user information:


user_id = 456  # Replace with the actual user ID
get_user(user_id)

To list all users:



list_users()

To change a user's password:



user_id = 789  # Replace with the actual user ID
new_password = "newpassword123"
change_password(user_id, new_password)

To validate user credentials:



username = "johndoe"
password = "password123"
validate_credentials(username, password)

To search users by email:



search_email = "john.doe@example.com"
search_users_by_email(search_email)

To update a user's role:


user_id = 123  # Replace with the actual user ID
new_role = "editor"
update_user_role(user_id, new_role)

To validate email uniqueness:


email = "test@example.com"
validate_email_uniqueness(email)

To disable a user account:


user_id = 123  # Replace with the actual user ID
disable_user(user_id)

To enable a user account:



user_id = 123  # Replace with the actual user ID
enable_user(user_id)

To count the total number of users:



    count_users()

Feel free to use these functions as needed, replacing the placeholders with actual data.
